{{refimprove|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox book | name = The Challenger Sale: Taking Control of the Customer Conversation | author = Matthew Dixon, Brent Adamson | language = English | country = United States | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = [[Penguin Group|Portfolio/Penguin]] | isbn = 9781591844358 | title_orig = | translator = | image = The Challenger Sale.jpg| image_size =298×450 | caption = Hardcover edition | cover_artist = | series = | release_date = November 10, 2011 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]]), [[E-book]] | pages = 240 pp. | dewey= | congress= | oclc= | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''The Challenger Sale''''' is the first non-fiction book by Matthew Dixon, Brent Adamson, and their colleagues at [[CEB Inc.]]. The book was published on November 10, 2011 by [[Penguin Group|Portfolio/Penguin]]. In the text, the book argues that relationship-building is no longer the best sales method. To sell complex, large-scale business-to-business solutions, customers are changing how they buy so sales people must change how they sell. The authors’ study found that sales reps fall into one of five profiles, and the challenger seller is the highest performer.<ref>{{cite web|author=Lisa Nirell|title=Trends In B2B Sales And Marketing From "The Challenger Sale"|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/3005114/trends-b2b-sales-and-marketing-challenger-sale|website=Fast Company|accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A 5-Minute Summary Of "The Challenger Sale" Book Your Boss Told You To Read|url=http://blog.hubspot.com/sales/challenger-sale-summary#sm.00000f7la2tpe0ea9wtu5l8bjrndr|website=Hubspot|accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>
==Reception== This book has been an Amazon best-seller in the Sales and Selling category.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amazon Best Sellers|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/bestsellers/books/2712|website=Amazon|accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>
